HEADWORD: Jargle
<hw>Jar"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OSw.
<ets>jerga</ets> to repeat angrily, to brawl, Icel. <ets>jarg</ets>
tedious iteration, F. <ets>jargonner</ets> to talk jargon. See
<er>Jargon</er> gabble.]</ety> <def>To emit a harsh or discordant
sound.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

